    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small television camera tubes of a particular kind, in which the image is formed on a transparent electrode coated with photoconductive material, the video signal being obtained from the variation in the current flowing to or from this as it is scanned by a beam of (usually low-speed) electrons.</Note_Text>
